The paper discusses the security of network function virtualization (NFV) and proposes a solution that combines NFV orchestration and quantum key distribution (QKD) technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the scheduling of an optical network using software-defined networking (SDN), which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different quantum links in a distributed environment, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the cost-effectiveness of the proposed solution, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a time-shared approach, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics and Automation).
